      "content": "Whoa, okay. I didn't mean to cause a stir, but that's a pretty bold claim if my engineer is looking at the same logs I am. If the root cause is truly fixed, can you walk me through how the patch handles the memory allocation process to prevent that corruption? I just need enough technical detail to satisfy our audit team so I can sign off on keeping the subscription. If I can't prove it's fixed, I can't justify the cost to my board.",
